  <h1>About SouthWesties ABQ</h1>

  <div class="card">
    <h2>Our Mission</h2>
    <p>SouthWesties ABQ is a 501(c)(3) nonprofit dedicated to growing West Coast Swing in New Mexico. We believe dance is for everyone — and we mean that. Our Thursday nights bring together beginners and experienced dancers alike in a space that's welcoming, non-competitive, and just plain fun.</p>
    <p>We're committed to a non-discriminatory environment for all participants regardless of race, ethnicity, age, gender, sexual orientation, skill level, or any other characteristic.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <h2>What Is West Coast Swing?</h2>
    <p>West Coast Swing is a partner dance characterized by its elastic, slotted style. It emerged from the California ballroom scene and has evolved into one of the most adaptable social dances in the world — it works with blues, pop, hip-hop, country, Latin, and virtually any other genre with a beat in 4:4 time.</p>
    <p>Because it's a social dance, there are no set routines. Leaders and followers improvise together, making each dance a unique conversation. That spontaneity is a big reason people fall in love with it.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <h2>Our Thursday Nights</h2>
    <p>Every Thursday at <a href="https://maps.google.com/?q=Lloyd+Shaw+Dance+Center,+5506+Coal+Ave+SE,+Albuquerque,+NM" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="link">Lloyd Shaw Dance Center</a> we run:</p>
    <ul class="styled-list">
      <li><strong>7:00–7:45 PM — Beginner Lesson:</strong> A structured intro to West Coast Swing basics. Assumes zero experience.</li>
      <li><strong>7:45–10:00 PM — Social Dance:</strong> Open floor for all levels. Music ranges from classic WCS to contemporary hits.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>You don't need a partner, and you don't need to have attended before. Just show up.</p>
  </div>

